Hey Guys, this year, we at mortorq 1515 are trying to migrate our previous swerve code, based of 364â€™s swerve code from the phoenix 5 api to the phoenix 6 api. We successfully updated firmware and replaced depreciated code with the new code, but we are having an issue. When enabled, if we try to run the angle motors at all, the swerve module will start rotating at its maximum speed and the angle will continue to accrue error for about 20 seconds until it stops. We believe this is caused due to failure to invert the motors correctly, although we setInverted in the config of each angle motor.

If anyone could help that would be wonderful. Our code is at GitHub - mortorqrobotics/BotterThanRevenge: 2024 Team 1515 FRC Robot Code . Thank you very much
